.\" cligPart DESCRIPTION
.SH DESCRIPTION
readfile reads a data file in one of PRESTO's many
recognized formats and displays its contents (or, for raw
observation formats, its header) on stdout.  It is a good first
command to run on any unfamiliar file, and is also the fastest way to
check things like a PSRFITS/filterbank header's frequency setup,
number of channels, or "Spectra per subint" (needed to know which
.B -downsamp
factors are valid for
.BR prepdata (1)
or
.BR prepsubband (1)).
.PP
The format is normally guessed from the filename's suffix (e.g.
.IR .dat ,
.IR .fft ,
.IR .fits/.sf ,
.IR .fil/.fb ,
a numeric PSRFITS-search-mode suffix, PRESTO
.I .cand
files, etc.); the explicit format flags
.RB ( -psrfits ,
.BR -filterbank ,
and, for old data from retired backends still occasionally
encountered,
.BR -pkmb / -bcpm / -wapp / -spigot )
override the guess when a file has been renamed or has no suffix.
For raw single-precision data types
.RB ( -float ,
.BR -double ,
.BR -short ,
etc.) readfile just dumps the requested range of values (see
.BR -index );
.B -page
paginates the output like
.BR more (1).

.\" cligPart DESCRIPTION end

